03/08/2010
ATHENS, Greece -- Finance Minister George Papaconstantinou ordered dozens of audits and formal inquiries into the activities of tax and customs officials on Monday (August 2nd), after receiving complaints about bribery, illegally acquired wealth, irregular inspections of business, omissions and VAT fraud. 
Ten audits will be carried out at institutes of technology education, hospitals, municipal authorities and enterprises, while 25 formal inquiries will be made regarding officials employed by the state financial services. 
(Eleftherotypia - 03/08/10; ANA-MPA, SKAI - 02/08/10)
